<!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
<section class="section" style="padding-bottom: 80px;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Frequently Asked Questions</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Everything you need to know.</h2>
    </div>
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          What makes Teamwork Commerce RFID different from competitors?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Teamwork Commerce offers the industry's only native end-to-end RFID stack — from source tagging and commissioning through checkout, loss prevention, and analytics. No third-party middleware required. New Black and NewStore offer unified commerce but require third-party integrations for deep RFID workflows. Our RFID is native to the core logic: every transaction (receiving, counting, transferring, selling) operates by individual EPC, not just UPC.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          What is the unit control ledger?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>The unit control ledger provides a complete transactional history for every individual EPC — where it was commissioned, received, counted, transferred, sold, and whitelisted. It's the foundation for accurate Available-to-Sell data and for the blacklist/whitelist system that powers EAS gate integration. Think of it as a "license plate" tracking system for every unit in your inventory.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does RFID loss prevention work with EAS gates?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Every EPC in the store is blacklisted by default. When a unit is sold at POS, it's instantly whitelisted. The POS communicates with a local server in the store that holds a copy of the unit control ledger, which pushes the whitelist update to the EAS gates via API. The signal reaches the gate before the customer does. We integrate with Checkpoint, Sensormatic, and other gate providers.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          What hardware do you support?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>We certify and support Bluebird RFID handhelds, Zebra, Impinj, and Honeywell readers, and Epson tag printers. We only promote equipment that has been tested and proven to work. The platform is hardware-agnostic across these certified brands and supports regional deployments across 40+ countries.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Can vendors pre-tag items, or do we need to commission tags in-store?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Both. The ideal approach is vendor source tagging at the point of manufacture. If that's not possible, Teamwork provides an integrated commissioning workflow inside the purchase receipt document — define quantity, print and encode tags, affix them, then RFID scan to populate the receipt with individual EPCs. One step, no separate process.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

